---
description: Run the right SitePilot E2E suite after code changes
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

After making code changes in this repository, run the smallest SitePilot E2E suite that matches the risk.

- Default to `npm run test:e2e:smoke`.
- Run `npm run test:e2e:content` when changes touch content planning, execution, post updates, image handling, WordPress write behavior, or `tests/e2e/`.
- Run `npm run test:e2e:all` for broad or cross-layer changes, E2E harness changes, fixture changes, or when the safest choice is to run everything.

Treat these paths as content-risky by default:

- `apps/desktop/src/main/`
- `packages/services/`
- `packages/contracts/`
- `packages/domain/`
- `packages/provider-adapters/`
- `plugins/wordpress-sitepilot/includes/Mcp/`
- `tests/e2e/`

The current suites mean:

- `test:e2e:smoke`: basic draft creation plus mixed core blocks with an image block
- `test:e2e:content`: smoke plus structured updates and creating a new draft with an attached image
- `test:e2e:all`: content plus screenshot-reference coverage

If the required suite cannot be run because the E2E WordPress environment or credentials are unavailable, state that clearly in the completion message.
